==English==

===Etymology===
''[[ham]] + [[shackle]]''

===Verb===
{{en-verb|hamshackles|hamshackling|hamshackled}}

#{{transitive}} To [[fasten]] (an animal) by a rope binding the head to one of the fore legs; as, to '''hamshackle''' a horse or cow; hence, to [[bind]] or [[restrain]]; to [[curb]].

